RONALD CLARK GREW UP LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS IN CHARGE OF CUSTODIAL WORK AT THE LIBRARY, AND KEPT IT VERY CLEARN.
AS A CHILD, YOUNG RONALD ONCE COMMENTED THAT HE WAS GLAD HIS FAMILY WAS RICH, AND HIS FATHER ALMOST SPIT OUT HIS FOOD.
THEY WEREN'T RICH; THEY WERE POOR.
HOWEVER, HIS FATHER ALWAYS TOOK PRIDE IN HIS WORK, INCLUDING WAXING THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES, SO THEY GLEAMED, EVEN FROM ABOVE.
AT FIRST, RONALD WAS ASHAMED OF LIVING IN THE LIBRARY, AND WOULDN'T INVITE OVER OTHER CHILDREN.
HOWEVER, LIVING IN THE LIBRARY CAME WITH ADVANTAGES.
DURING THE DAY, YOU HAD TO BE QUIET, BUT AT NIGHT YOU COULD RUN AND YELL AND ACTUALLY HAD A LOT OF FREEDOM IN A BIG, UNIQUE SPACE.
PLUS, ANYTHING YOU WANTED TO KNOW, YOU COULD LOOK UP.
IT WAS GROWING UP IN THE LIBRARY THAT INSTILLED IN PROF.
CLARK A LIFELONG LOVE OF LEARNING.
AS AN ADULT, HE WAS THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO HIGH SCHOOL, MUCH LESS COLLEGE.
HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS OFFICE ONE DAY, AND THE SIGN ON THE DOOR THAT SAID, "PROF CLARK".
HIS DAD DIDN'T GIVE MUCH OUTWARD SIGN, BUT THE LOOK IN HIS EYE TOLD HOW PROUD HE WAS.
IN THE END, THE THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE THAT PROF CLARK DEVELOPED GROWING UP IN THE LIBRARY HELPED HIM TO BE THE SUCCESSFUL ADULT HE BECAME.
RONALD JONES GREW UP LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS THE LIBRARY CUSTODIAN.
AS A CHILD, RONALD ONCE COMMENTED THAT HE WAS GLAD HIS FAMILY WAS RICH, AND HIS FATHER ALMOST SPIT OUT HIS FOOD.
HIS MOTHER TOLD HIM THEY WEREN'T, IN FACT, RICH.
HIS FATHER TOLD HIM THEY WERE POOR.
HIS FATHER TOOK GREAT PRIDE IN HIS WORK, AND THE LIBRARY WAS SPOTLESS.
HIS FATHER EVEN WAXED THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES SO THEY GLEAMED.
RONALD WAS EMBARRASSED TO BE POOR AND LIVE AT THE LIBRARY, AND NEVER INVITED OTHER KIDS OVER.
HOWEVER, LIVING IN THE LIBRARY CAME WITH ADVANTAGES.
EVEN THOUGH YOU HAD TO BE QUIET DURING THE DAY, AT NIGHT RONALD COULD RUN AND YELL AND PLAY IN THE OPEN SPACE AMONG ALL THE BOOKS.
HE WOULD OFTEN STAY UP LATE AND COULD LOOK UP THE ANSWER TO ANY QUESTION HE HAD.
HAVING ALL THIS KNOWLEDGE AT HIS FINGERTIPS INSTILLED IN RONALD A LIFELONG LOVE OF LEARNING.
NONE OF THE OTHER MEMBERS OF HIS FAMILY HAD GRADUATED FROM HIGH SCHOOL, BUT RONALD GRADUATED FROM COLLEGE AND WENT ON TO BECOME A PROFESSOR.
HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS OFFICE ONE DAY, AND THOUGH HIS FATHER DIDN'T SAY MUCH, HE COULD TELL THAT HIS FATHER WAS PROUD AND IT MEANT A LOT TO HIM.
GROWING UP LIVING IN THE LIBRARY INSTILLED A LOVE OF LEARNING IN RONALD THAT LED TO HIS SUCCESS AS AN ADULT.
